The AI-Based Lecture Summarizer is designed to help college students automatically convert lecture audio into concise and structured notes. Students often struggle to take effective notes during fast-paced lectures, which leads to loss of important information and reduced learning efficiency.
This system uses speech recognition to convert recorded lecture audio into text and then applies Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques to generate meaningful summaries. The final output includes key points, short summaries, and important highlights from the lecture.
The solution aims to improve learning productivity by saving time, enhancing understanding, and providing easily revisable notes. It can also assist students who miss classes or have difficulty following lectures in real time..
